e CI guard on `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` meant local runs got NO isolation.\\n\\n8. User asked about sandboxing via Claude Code docs - I fetched the docs and explained sandboxing only restricts tool execution, not the context load chain.\\n\\n9. User confirmed sandboxing won't help with context loading. We agreed the fix is `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` isolation.\\n\\n10. User asked if we even need to copy anything from ~/.claude/ - since Keychain auth works without files, the answer was no (locally). On CI, only `.claude.json` is needed.\\n\\n11. User said \\\"let's try it\\\" - I invoked tdd-dev skill, then implemented the fix.\\n\\n12. User rejected writing tests for test harness code - \\\"we don't need to test our test harness code directly...\\\"\\n\\n13. I made the changes directly:\\n    - Replaced `isolatedConfigDir()` with `cleanConfigDir()` \\n    - Always set `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR`\\n    - On CI: symlink only `.claude.json`\\n    - Locally: empty dir\\n    - Fixed `nilerr` lint issue by nesting the error check\\n    - Fixed `err :=` redeclaration issue with `err =`\\n\\n14. User asked to commit, then look at another artifact. Committed and examined `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/e2e/artifacts/2026-02-26T12-25-30`.\\n\\n15. New artifact showed ALL 5 failures had Claude Code onboarding flow (theme picker, login). Empty config dir meant no `hasCompletedOnboarding: true`.\\n\\n16. Fixed by writing minimal `.claude.json` with `hasCompletedOnboarding` locally. On CI, the symlinked `.claude.json` from Bootstrap already has it.\\n\\n17. User asked about WaitFor race condition. I investigated tmux.go and found the race: Send() snapshots pre-echo state, WaitFor matches ❯ in echoed input, contentChanged fires because echo IS in stable content, settles for 2s while agent hasn't started.\\n\\n18. User asked if the fix would impact other agents. I traced through Claude (affected), Gemini (not affected - pattern disappears), OpenCode (not affected). Fix is safe.\\n\\n19. User confirmed, I implemented post-echo snapshot in Send().\\n\\n20. User asked about E2E_ENTIRE_BIN - does it affect hooks? Investigation confirmed hooks call bare `entire` from PATH, not the test binary.\\n\\n21. User suggested altering PATH. I added PATH prepend in TestMain. User confirmed it's process-scoped only.\\n\\n22. User asked to show preflight info. I added binary path, PATH resolution, version to entire-version.txt and stderr.\\n\\n23. User noted gotestsum swallows stderr. I moved info to artifact file and added cat after test report.\\n\\n24. User asked to print version info at end after report and show artifacts dir again.\\n\\n25. User asked to refactor mise.toml duplication. I extracted `mise-tasks/test-e2e` script with E2E_PARALLEL support. Fixed shellcheck issue with quoting.\\n\\n26. User pointed out `entire binary:` and `entire (PATH):` are the same (redundant after PATH fix), and artifacts dir printed twice. I removed the redundant PATH line and artifact dir from preflight.\\n\\n27. User asked about E2E_PARALLEL - I explained it parameterized Gemini's `-parallel 1`. User corrected me about TimeoutMultiplier (just for slowness) vs RegisterGate (actual queueing). User wants gate size configurable from outside for CI with higher rate limits.\\n\\n28. I proposed per-agent env vars. User said \\\"just use E2E_CONCURRENT_TEST_LIMIT global\\\".\\n\\n29. I implemented, user also wanted Gemini default changed from 3 to 2. Dropped E2E_PARALLEL entirely.\\n\\nCurrent state: 7 commits on `alex/more-e2e-fixes`, PR #508 open.\\n\\nBranch commits:\\n1. d3409a7c2 - Isolate E2E from user settings\\n2. 2db3e1736 - hasCompletedOnboarding \\n3. 6ddd69c8b - Post-echo snapshot WaitFor fix\\n4. 77af66f51 - PATH prepend for hooks\\n5. 5e77aee07 - Preflight info + mise refactor\\n6. dae0aca25 - Remove redundant PATH line and artifact dir\\n7. cf6a6ede0 - E2E_CONCURRENT_TEST_LIMIT gate override\\n\\nSummary:\\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\\n   The user invoked `/debug-e2e` to diagnose E2E test failures across two test runs. The initial failing run (`2026-02-26T11-45-27`) had 5 failures while a subsequent run (`2026-02-26T12-02-11`) passed all 37 tests. The user wanted to understand whether failures were from non-deterministic agent behavior or something else. This evolved into a comprehensive E2E infrastructure hardening effort addressing: user settings isolation, onboarding flow bypass, WaitFor race conditions, binary PATH resolution for hooks, preflight diagnostics, mise task deduplication, and configurable concurrency gates. A PR was created (#508) on branch `alex/more-e2e-fixes`.\\n\\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\\n   - E2E test isolation via `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` environment variable\\n   - Claude Code onboarding flow (`hasCompletedOnboarding` in `.claude.json`)\\n   - tmux-based interactive agent sessions with `Send()`/`WaitFor()` pattern matching\\n   - Post-echo terminal snapshot to prevent false pattern matches\\n   - Git hook invocation PATH resolution (hooks call bare `entire`, not full path)\\n   - `RegisterGate` concurrency semaphore for per-agent test parallelism\\n   - `E2E_CONCURRENT_TEST_LIMIT` env var to override gate size in CI\\n   - mise task file-based scripts (`mise-tasks/test-e2e`) vs TOML inline tasks\\n   - `stableContent()` strips last 3 terminal lines to ignore TUI status bar\\n   - `settleTime` (2s) and `pollInterval` (500ms) constants for WaitFor\\n\\n3. Files and Code Sections:\\n\\n   - **`e2e/agents/claude.go`** — Core fix for user settings isolation\\n     - Replaced `isolatedConfigDir()` (symlinked everything from `~/.claude/` except CLAUDE.md and skills/) with `cleanConfigDir()` (empty temp dir)\\n     - Always sets `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` (removed `CI` guard)\\n     - On CI: symlinks only `.claude.json` for API key auth\\n     - Locally: writes `{\\\"hasCompletedOnboarding\\\":true}` to skip onboarding\\n     - `RunPrompt` and `StartSession` both use `cleanConfigDir()`\\n     ```go\\n     func cleanConfigDir() (string, error) {\\n         dst, err := os.MkdirTemp(\\\"\\\", \\\"claude-config-*\\\")\\n         if err != nil {\\n             return \\\"\\\", err\\n         }\\n         if os.Getenv(\\\"CI\\\") != \\\"\\\" {\\n             if home, err := os.UserHomeDir(); err == nil {\\n                 src := filepath.Join(home, \\\".claude\\\", \\\".claude.json\\\")\\n                 if _, err := os.Stat(src); err == nil {\\n                     _ = os.Symlink(src, filepath.Join(dst, \\\".claude.json\\\"))\\n                 }\\n             }\\n         } else {\\n             _ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dst, \\\".claude.json\\\"),\\n                 []byte(`{\\\"hasCompletedOnboarding\\\":true}`), 0o644)\\n         }\\n         return dst, nil\\n     }\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`e2e/agents/tmux.go`** — WaitFor race condition fix\\n     - `Send()` now waits for terminal echo to render before snapshotting `stableAtSend`\\n     - Polls up to 5s for content to change from pre-send state, then captures post-echo snapshot\\n     - This prevents `WaitFor(\\\"❯\\\")` from matching the `❯` in echoed user input\\n     ```go\\n     func (s *TmuxSession) Send(input string) error {\\n         preSend := stableContent(s.Capture())\\n         if err := s.SendKeys(input); err != nil {\\n             return err\\n         }\\n         time.Sleep(200 * time.Millisecond)\\n         if err := s.SendKeys(\\\"Enter\\\"); err != nil {\\n             return err\\n         }\\n         deadline := time.Now().Add(5 * time.Second)\\n         for time.Now().Before(deadline) {\\n             time.Sleep(200 * time.Millisecond)\\n             current := stableContent(s.Capture())\\n             if current != preSend {\\n                 s.stableAtSend = current\\n                 return nil\\n             }\\n         }\\n         s.stableAtSend = stableContent(s.Capture())\\n         return nil\\n     }\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`e2e/tests/main_test.go`** — PATH prepend and preflight info\\n     - Prepends test