title\\\":\\\"Configuration · Gemini\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://gemini-testing.github.io/doc/config.html\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Gemini CLI Configuration | Gemini CLI\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://gemini-cli-docs.pages.dev/cli/configuration\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"How to change gemini cli directory - CometAPI - All AI Models in One API\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.cometapi.com/how-to-change-gemini-cli-directory/\\\"}]\\n\\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Gemini CLI configuration directory settings:\\n\\n## Configuration Directory Location\\n\\nGemini CLI configuration files are stored in a dedicated `.gemini` directory within your home directory at `~/.gemini/`.\\n\\n## GEMINI_CONFIG_DIR Environment Variable\\n\\nThe GEMINI_CONFIG_DIR environment variable is used to specify a custom path for the .gemini config directory. However, it's important to note that GEMINI_CONFIG_DIR has been requested and referenced in code, but platform-specific bugs and inconsistent behavior (particularly on Windows) have been reported, meaning environment-variable-based redirection may not be uniformly reliable on every platform or release.\\n\\n## Alternative Configuration Directory Option\\n\\nInstead of GEMINI_CONFIG_DIR, there's a more reliable environment variable: GEMINI_CLI_HOME specifies the root directory for Gemini CLI's user-level configuration and storage, which by default is the user's system home directory, and the CLI will create a .gemini folder inside this directory.\\n\\n## Current Status\\n\\nCurrently, the Gemini CLI hardcodes the configuration directory to .gemini within the user's home directory, which limits flexibility for users who may wish to store configuration files in a different location. There has been a feature request (Issue #2815) to make the configuration directory configurable via environment variable.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"49