kills/, tools/, and themes/.\\n\\n### Loading Order and Precedence\\nConfig sources are loaded in this order (later sources override earlier ones): Remote config (from .well-known/opencode) - organizational defaults · Global config (~/.config/opencode/opencode.json) - user preferences · Custom config (OPENCODE_CONFIG env var) - custom overrides · Project config (opencode.json in project) - project-specific settings\\n\\nThe custom directory is loaded after the global config and .opencode directories, so it can override their settings.\\n\\n### Usage Example\\nYou can use it like: export OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR=/path/to/my/config-directory opencode run \\\"Hello world\\\"\\n\\n### Benefits\\nThe OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR environment variable adds flexibility for power users, portable installations, or testing scenarios where a specific config location is needed regardless of the OS default.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"b159fd83-b56e-461d-9416-4ba39f160fe1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T03:42:23.701Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"Search the web or documentation for where Gemini CLI and OpenCode store their user-level configuration/settings that could affect behavior (system prompts, plugins, etc.). Specifically:\\n\\n1. Gemini CLI (`gemini`) - where does it store user config? Is there a `GEMINI_CONFIG_DIR` or similar env var? Check `~/.gemini/` or similar.\\n2. OpenCode (`opencode`) - where does it store user config? Is there an `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or similar env var? Check `~/.opencode/` or similar.\\n\\nI want to know if these agents could pick up user-level settings (custom instructions, plugins, etc.) that would affect E2E test behavior, similar to how Claude Code picks up `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`.\",\"agentId\":\"aa01928005316d187\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01EDVHXcq6t1JpNAa8LUV78M\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01PY1pjFHWfUFQVWjzuBgHZu\",\"