?\\n\\nCheck the OpenCode documentation at opencode.ai/docs and any GitHub issues about auto-commit behavior.\",\"agentId\":\"a2a0d324c2c79e090\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01DZcvLxdLMHYzZWs5nNf7kx\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_017XNpH18PMtXdcCqiqH8Qw8\",\"uuid\":\"84b3762c-f716-442c-a5dd-b5aeb79e520e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T04:04:06.718Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"84b3762c-f716-442c-a5dd-b5aeb79e520e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d9f0a13a-2256-4ef2-a6ed-7fe605e55655\",\"version\":\"2.1.58\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/more-e2e-fixes\",\"slug\":\"ticklish-zooming-robin\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Task\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_017XNpH18PMtXdcCqiqH8Qw8\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_017XNpH18PMtXdcCqiqH8Qw8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T04:04:36.953Z\",\"uuid\":\"0f5e732a-7a9a-4aeb-ac0d-4c533b37e96f\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"779d3abc-6750-4b56-9c5e-4f68c0710abe\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d9f0a13a-2256-4ef2-a6ed-7fe605e55655\",\"version\":\"2.1.58\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/more-e2e-fixes\",\"slug\":\"ticklish-zooming-robin\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_017XNpH18PMtXdcCqiqH8Qw8\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here is a comprehensive summary of my findings:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## OpenCode CLI: Auto-Commit / Auto-Git Configuration Options\\n\\n### 1. Does OpenCode have a setting to prevent automatic git commands?\\n\\n**Yes.** OpenCode does not have a single toggle to disable \\\"auto-commit,\\\" but it provides a granular **permissions system** that can block, prompt, or allow specific bash commands -- including all git operations. Since OpenCode has **no dedicated git tool** (all git operations run through the `bash` tool), controlling bash permissions is the mechanism for controlling git behavior.\\n\\nThe recommended configuration in `opencode.json`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"permission\\\": {\\n    \\\"bash\\\": {\\n      \\\"*\\\": \\\"allow\\\",\\n      \\\"git commit *\\\": \\\"deny\\\",\\n      \\\"git push *\\\": \\\"deny\\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe three permission actions are:\\n- **`\\\"allow\\\"`** -- executes without approval\\n- **`\\\"ask\\\"`** -- prompts the user for confirmation before executing\\n- **`\\\"deny\\\"`** -- blocks the action entirely\\n\\nTo disable ALL git operations:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"permission\\\": {\\n    \\\"bash\\\": {\\n      \\\"*\\\": \\\"allow\\\",\\n      \\\"git *\\\": \\\"deny\\\",\\n      \\\"git status *\\\": \\\"allow\\\",\\n      \\\"git diff *\\\": \\\"allow\\\",\\n      \\\"git log *\\\": \\\"allow\\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe last matching rule wins, so you can deny `git *` broadly and then re-allow safe read-only commands.\\n\\n### 2. Is there an `opencode.json` config option or environment variable?\\n\\n**Config file: Yes. Environment variable: No.**\\n\\n- **`opencode.json`** in the project root (highest precedence) or `~/.config/opencode/opencode.json` (global) supports the `permission` key with nested bash command patterns as shown above.\\n- There is **no environment variable** like `OPENCODE_DISABLE_AUTOCOMMIT`. The environment variables that exist (`OPENCODE_DISABLE_AUTOUPDATE`, `OPENCODE_DISABLE_PRUNE`, `OPENCODE_DISABLE_AUTOCOMPACT`) are unrelated to git.\\n\\n**Important note about the default behavior:** OpenCode's built-in bash tool system prompt (in `bash.txt`) contains instructions telling the LLM to format git commits with a co-author line (`Co-Authored-By: opencode <noreply@opencode.ai>`) and a \\\"Generated with opencode\\\" footer. This means the LLM is *instructed* to commit in a certain style, but the actual auto-commit behavior is driven by the LLM deciding to run `git commit` via the bash tool. It is not a deterministic, built-in auto-commit feature -- it is an emergent behavior from the system prompt instructions.\\n\\nThis is why using **permissions** (which are deterministic and enforced before tool execution) is the reliable way to control this, rather than relying on rules/instructions (which the LLM may ignore, as documented in [Issue #3239](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues/3239)).\\n\\n### 3. Does OpenCode have \\\"modes\\\" or \\\"agent\\\" configurations that control auto-commit?\\n\\n**Modes:** OpenCode has two built-in modes:\\n- **Build** (default) -- all tools enabled, including bash (and thus git)\\n- **Plan** -- disables `write`, `edit`, `patch`, and `bash` tools entirely. Since git runs through bash, Plan mode effectively prevents all git operations, but it also prevents all shell commands.\\n\\nYou can create **custom modes** (in `.opencode/modes/`) that selectively disable the bash tool, but this is a blunt instrument since it blocks all shell commands, not just git.\\n\\n**Agents:** Agent-level permission overrides are supported:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"permission\\\": {\\n    \\\"bash\\\": {\\n      \\\"git *\\\": \\\"allow\\\"\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"agent\\\": {\\n    \\\"review\\\": {\\n      \\\"permission\\\": {\\n        \\\"bash\\\": {\\n          \\\"git *\\\": \\\"deny\\\"\\n        }\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAgent permissions merge with and override global permissions, so you can have one agent that can commit and another that cannot.\\n\\n### Summary Table\\n\\n| Mechanism | Granularity | Reliability | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| `permission.bash` with `\\\"deny\\\"` | Per-command pattern | Deterministic | Recommended approach |\\n| `permission.bash` with `\\\"ask\\\"` | Per-command pattern | Deterministic | Prompts before each git command |\\n| Rules/instructions (\\\"never commit\\\") | LLM instruction | Unreliable | LLM may ignore; documented in issues |\\n| Plan mode | All bash disabled | Deterministic | Too broad; blocks all shell commands |\\n| Agent-level permissions | Per-agent | Deterministic | Useful for multi-agent setups |\\n\\n### Key Caveat\\n\\nAfter changing `opencode.json` permissions, OpenCode **requires a restart** -- hot-reloading of permission config is not supported (confirmed by maintainers in [Issue #3239](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues/3239)).\\n\\n---\\n\\nSources:\\n- [OpenCode Config Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/config/)\\n- [OpenCode Permissions Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/permissions/)\\n- [OpenCode Agents Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/agents/)\\n- [OpenCode Modes Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/modes/)\\n- [OpenCode Tools Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/tools/)\\n- [OpenCode CLI Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/cli/)\\n- [Issue #3239: Agent is auto-committing despite instructions](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues/3239)\\n- [Issue #1467: Ability to disable git commands](https://github.com/sst/opencode/issues/1467)\\n- [Issue #786: OpenCode automatically creating git commits](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues/786)\\n- [Issue #919: Disabling co-authoring](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues/919)\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a2a0d324c2c79e090 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 30558\\ntool_uses: 23\\nduration_ms: 158063</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"70c573ab-dc04-4bfb-a981-3ffb25f3be4c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T04:04:36.948Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"Search the web for OpenCode CLI (opencode.ai) configuration options to disable auto-commit or auto-git behavior. Specifically:\\n\\n1. Does OpenCode have a setting to prevent it from automatically running git commands (add/commit)?\\n2. Is there an `opencode.json` config option or environment variable to control this?\\n3. Does OpenCod